-- China shares down on weak property, losses limited by FTZ stocks
-- 
-- Thu Apr 17, 2014 03:10AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, April 17 (Reuters) - China shares closed down on Thursday, pulled lower by weak real estate shares as investors braced themselves ahead of housing data expected to show property price growth slowed in March.

The Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> ended down 0.3 percent at 2,098.88 points. The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings fell 0.4 percent. Shares in China Fortune Land Co Ltd <600340.SS> were down 3.6 percent, while Metro Land Corp Ltd <600683.SS> lost 1.5 percent, and Beijing Capital Development Co Ltd <600376.SS> shed 2.0 percent. March housing data will be released on Friday.